## Example

The following example generates C4533. To resolve the issue, move the initialization before the jump instruction or after the target of the jump.

```cpp
// C4533.cpp
// compile with: /W1
#include <stdio.h>

struct A
{
   int m_data;
};

int main()
{
   if (1)
   {
      goto Label;
   }

   A a = { 100 };

   Label:   // C4533
      printf("\n%d", a.m_data);   // prints an uninitialized value
}
```

